            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "2Kgs.8:1-9:13",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3E2%20Kings%208%3A1-9%3A13%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_8_1%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E2%20Kings%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EThe%20Woman%20from%20Shunem%20Returns%20Home%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EElisha%20had%20told%20the%20woman%20whose%20son%20he%20had%20brought%20back%20to%20life%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BTake%20your%20family%20and%20move%20to%20some%20other%20place%2C%20for%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20has%20called%20for%20a%20famine%20on%20Israel%20that%20will%20last%20for%20seven%20years.%26%23x201D%3B%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_8_2%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20the%20woman%20did%20as%20the%20man%20of%20God%20instructed.%20She%20took%20her%20family%20and%20settled%20in%20the%20land%20of%20the%20Philistines%20for%20seven%20years.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_8_3%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EAfter%20the%20famine%20ended%20she%20returned%20from%20the%20land%20of%20the%20Philistines%2C%20and%20she%20went%20to%20see%20the%20king%20about%20getting%20back%20her%20house%20and%20land.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_8_4%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EAs%20she%20came%20in%2C%20the%20king%20was%20talking%20with%20Gehazi%2C%20the%20servant%20of%20the%20man%20of%20God.%20The%20king%20had%20just%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BTell%20me%20some%20stories%20about%20the%20great%20things%20Elisha%20has%20done.%26%23x201D%3B%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_8_5%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EAnd%20Gehazi%20was%20telling%20the%20king%20about%20the%20time%20Elisha%20had%20brought%20a%20boy%20back%20to%20life.%20At%20that%20very%20moment%2C%20the%20mother%20of%20the%20boy%20walked%20in%20to%20make%20her%20appeal%20to%20the%20king%20about%20her%20house%20and%20land.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%26%23x201C%3BLook%2C%20my%20lord%20the%20king!%26%23x201D%3B%20Gehazi%20exclaimed.%20%26%23x201C%3BHere%20is%20the%20woman%20now%2C%20and%20this%20is%20her%20son%26%23x2014%3Bthe%20very%20one%20Elisha%20brought%20back%20to%20life!%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_8_6%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BIs%20this%20true%3F%26%23x201D%3B%20the%20king%20asked%20her.%20And%20she%20told%20him%20the%20story.%20So%20he%20directed%20one%20of%20his%20officials%20to%20see%20that%20everything%20she%20had%20lost%20was%20restored%20to%20her%2C%20including%20the%20value%20of%20any%20crops%20that%20had%20been%20harvested%20during%20her%20absence.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_8_7%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EHazael%20Murders%20Ben-Hadad%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EElisha%20went%20to%20Damascus%2C%20the%20capital%20of%20Aram%2C%20where%20King%20Ben-hadad%20lay%20sick.%20When%20someone%20told%20the%20king%20that%20the%20man%20of%20God%20had%20come%2C%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_8_8%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3Ethe%20king%20said%20to%20Hazael%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BTake%20a%20gift%20to%20the%20man%20of%20God.%20Then%20tell%20him%20to%20ask%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20%26%23x2018%3BWill%20I%20recover%20from%20this%20illness%3F%26%23x2019%3B%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_8_9%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20Hazael%20loaded%20down%20forty%20camels%20with%20the%20finest%20products%20of%20Damascus%20as%20a%20gift%20for%20Elisha.%20He%20went%20to%20him%20and%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BYour%20servant%20Ben-hadad%2C%20the%20king%20of%20Aram%2C%20has%20sent%20me%20to%20ask%2C%20%26%23x2018%3BWill%20I%20recover%20from%20this%20illness%3F%26%23x2019%3B%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_8_10%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EAnd%20Elisha%20replied%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BGo%20and%20tell%20him%2C%20%26%23x2018%3BYou%20will%20surely%20recover.%26%23x2019%3B%20But%20actually%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20has%20shown%20me%20that%20he%20will%20surely%20die!%26%23x201D%3B%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_8_11%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3EElisha%20stared%20at%20Hazael%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E8%3A11a%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3EHe%20stared%20at%20him.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20with%20a%20fixed%20gaze%20until%20Hazael%20became%20uneasy.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E8%3A11b%3C%2Fspan%3E%20The%20meaning%20of%20the%20Hebrew%20is%20uncertain.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Then%20the%20man%20of%20God%20started%20weeping.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_8_12%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BWhat%26%23x2019%3Bs%20the%20matter%2C%20my%20lord%3F%26%23x201D%3B%20Hazael%20asked%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3EElisha%20replied%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BI%20know%20the%20terrible%20things%20you%20will%20do%20to%20the%20people%20of%20Israel.%20You%20will%20burn%20their%20fortified%20cities%2C%20kill%20their%20young%20men%20with%20the%20sword%2C%20dash%20their%20little%20children%20to%20the%20ground%2C%20and%20rip%20open%20their%20pregnant%20women!%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_8_13%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3EHazael%20responded%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BHow%20could%20a%20nobody%20like%20me%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E8%3A13%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Ea%20dog.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20ever%20accomplish%20such%20great%20things%3F%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3EElisha%20answered%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BThe%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20has%20shown%20me%20that%20you%20are%20going%20to%20be%20the%20king%20of%20Aram.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_8_14%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20Hazael%20left%20Elisha%20and%20went%20back%2C%20the%20king%20asked%20him%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BWhat%20did%20Elisha%20tell%20you%3F%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3EAnd%20Hazael%20replied%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BHe%20told%20me%20that%20you%20will%20surely%20recover.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_8_15%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20the%20next%20day%20Hazael%20took%20a%20blanket%2C%20soaked%20it%20in%20water%2C%20and%20held%20it%20over%20the%20king%26%23x2019%3Bs%20face%20until%20he%20died.%20Then%20Hazael%20became%20the%20next%20king%20of%20Aram.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_8_16%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EJehoram%20Rules%20in%20Judah%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3EJehoram%20son%20of%20King%20Jehoshaphat%20of%20Judah%20began%20to%20rule%20over%20Judah%20in%20the%20fifth%20year%20of%20the%20reign%20of%20Joram%20son%20of%20Ahab%2C%20king%20of%20Israel.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_8_17%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3EJehoram%20was%20thirty-two%20years%20old%20when%20he%20became%20king%2C%20and%20he%20reigned%20in%20Jerusalem%20eight%20years.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_8_18%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20Jehoram%20followed%20the%20example%20of%20the%20kings%20of%20Israel%20and%20was%20as%20wicked%20as%20King%20Ahab%2C%20for%20he%20had%20married%20one%20of%20Ahab%26%23x2019%3Bs%20daughters.%20So%20Jehoram%20did%20what%20was%20evil%20in%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20sight.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_8_19%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%2219%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20did%20not%20want%20to%20destroy%20Judah%2C%20for%20he%20had%20promised%20his%20servant%20David%20that%20his%20descendants%20would%20continue%20to%20rule%2C%20shining%20like%20a%20lamp%20forever.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_8_20%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%2220%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E20%3C%2Fspan%3EDuring%20Jehoram%26%23x2019%3Bs%20reign%2C%20the%20Edomites%20revolted%20against%20Judah%20and%20crowned%20their%20own%20king.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_8_21%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%2221%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E21%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20Jehoram%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E8%3A21a%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3EJoram%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20a%20variant%20spelling%20of%20Jehoram%3B%20also%20in%208%3A23%2C%2024.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20went%20with%20all%20his%20chariots%20to%20attack%20the%20town%20of%20Zair.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E8%3A21b%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Greek%20version%20reads%20%3Cem%3ESeir.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20The%20Edomites%20surrounded%20him%20and%20his%20chariot%20commanders%2C%20but%20he%20went%20out%20at%20night%20and%20attacked%20them%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E8%3A21c%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3Ehe%20went%20out%20and%20escaped.%3C%2Fem%3E%20The%20meaning%20of%20the%20Hebrew%20is%20uncertain.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20under%20cover%20of%20darkness.%20But%20Jehoram%26%23x2019%3Bs%20army%20deserted%20him%20and%20fled%20to%20their%20homes.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_8_22%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%2222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E22%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20Edom%20has%20been%20independent%20from%20Judah%20to%20this%20day.%20The%20town%20of%20Libnah%20also%20revolted%20about%20that%20same%20time.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_8_23%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%2223%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22bod